xceptionally informed and balanced view of the Gulag.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aForced laborzSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aInternment campszSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aPolitical prisonerszSoviet Union. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aConquest, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHabeck, Mary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRadosh, Ronald, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSevostianov, Grigory, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z978311053801440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016064240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300160642423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300160642/original  a978-3-11-053801-4  Yale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles